### 6. General Discussion: How to Model in SDF
*   Ari Keränen and Bart suggested that the working group needs an informational guidance document on how to model things using SDF, to preserve institutional knowledge gained from NIPC and other implementations.
*   Elliot Lear suggested that instead of a traditional IETF document, this would be better served by interactive developer resources, such as a dedicated portal (e.g., an "sdf.io" website) populated with simple code snippets, demo programs, and "vibe-coded" examples (e.g., how to control a light).
*   Daniel Smolon strongly supported these ideas, stating that clear examples would make SDF significantly more accessible to external groups looking to build on the technology.

